---
import MainLayout from '../../../layouts/docs-layout.astro';
const codeExample1 = `git push origin main
→ Cloudflare Pages triggers
→ Astro build (30s)
→ Pages deploys globally
→ Live instantly
→ 0 cost`;

const codeExample2 = `// wrangler.toml
[env.production]
routes = [
  { pattern = "api.example.com/*", zone_name = "example.com" }
]

// src/index.ts
export default {
  async fetch(request) {
    const auth = request.headers.get('Authorization')
    if (!auth) return new Response('Unauthorized', { status: 401 })

    // Route to D1 database
    const db = env.DB
    const result = await db.prepare(
      'SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = ?'
    ).bind(userId).first()

    return Response.json(result)
  }
}`;

const codeExample3 = `// Create D1 database
wrangler d1 create production

// Schema: 3 tables, 2 indexes
CREATE TABLE users (
  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  email TEXT UNIQUE,
  mcu_balance INT DEFAULT 0,
  created_at DATETIME
);

CREATE TABLE missions (
  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id TEXT,
  status TEXT,
  cost_mcu INT,
  FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(id)
);`;

const codeExample4 = `// Cache JWT tokens with 1hr expiry
const token = 'eyJhbGc...'
await env.KV.put('token:' + user_id, token, {
  expirationTtl: 3600
})

// Rate limiting: 100 requests per minute
const key = 'ratelimit:' + user_id + ':' + minute
const count = await env.KV.get(key) || 0
if (count > 100) return new Response('Too many', { status: 429 })
await env.KV.put(key, count + 1, { expirationTtl: 60 })`;
---
<MainLayout title="How We Built a SaaS with $0/mo Infrastructure" description="Technical breakdown of using Cloudflare Workers, D1, KV, Pages & Workers AI to run a production SaaS at zero infrastructure cost. Real numbers from Mekong RaaS.">
  <article class="blog-post" style="max-width:800px;margin:0 auto;padding:2rem">
    <h1 class="gradient-text">How We Built a SaaS with $0/mo Infrastructure</h1>
    <p style="color:var(--md-sys-color-on-surface-variant);margin-bottom:2rem">Published March 21, 2026 · 8 min read</p>

    <section style="margin-bottom:2rem">
      <h2>The Problem: SaaS Economics Are Broken</h2>
      <p>Traditional SaaS costs before you serve a single customer:</p>
      <ul style="color:var(--md-sys-color-on-surface-variant);line-height:1.8">
        <li><strong>AWS/GCP/Azure:</strong> $100-500/mo just for minimum viable infrastructure</li>
        <li><strong>Database:</strong> $20-100/mo (even small Postgres instances)</li>
        <li><strong>Storage:</strong> $10-50/mo (S3, GCS)</li>
        <li><strong>Monitoring/Logging:</strong> $50-200/mo (Datadog, New Relic)</li>
        <li><strong>Total baseline:</strong> ~$500/mo before a single paying customer</li>
      </ul>
      <p>This kills bootstrapping. Most founders abandon SaaS ideas because the fixed costs are too high.</p>
    </section>

    <section style="margin-bottom:2rem">
      <h2>Our Stack: Cloudflare's Free Tier Superpower</h2>
      <p>We built Mekong RaaS on Cloudflare's edge network. Here's why it's the game-changer:</p>

      <h3 style="font-size:1.1rem;margin-top:1.5rem">1. Cloudflare Pages ($0)</h3>
      <p>Frontend hosting with unlimited requests, auto-HTTPS, instant deployment from git.</p>
      <pre style="background:var(--md-sys-color-surface-container);padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;overflow-x:auto;font-size:0.85rem;margin:1rem 0"><code>{codeExample1}</code></pre>

      <h3 style="font-size:1.1rem;margin-top:1.5rem">2. Cloudflare Workers ($0/month standard)</h3>
      <p>Edge functions. Deploy API endpoints globally. 100K free requests/day. After that, $0.50 per 1M requests.</p>
      <pre style="background:var(--md-sys-color-surface-container);padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;overflow-x:auto;font-size:0.85rem;margin:1rem 0"><code>{codeExample2}</code></pre>
      <p><strong>Our volume:</strong> 50K API calls/day in beta → $0 cost. We don't pay until 100K+.</p>

      <h3 style="font-size:1.1rem;margin-top:1.5rem">3. Cloudflare D1 (SQLite on Edge) ($0)</h3>
      <p>Distributed SQLite with instant global replication. No VPC, no scaling limits on free tier.</p>
      <pre style="background:var(--md-sys-color-surface-container);padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;overflow-x:auto;font-size:0.85rem;margin:1rem 0"><code>{codeExample3}</code></pre>
      <p><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Zero cold-start latency. SQL is fast on edge. No database connection pooling needed.</p>

      <h3 style="font-size:1.1rem;margin-top:1.5rem">4. Cloudflare KV (Global Cache) ($0)</h3>
      <p>Distributed key-value store for session tokens, rate limiting, user preferences. 100K free ops/day.</p>
      <pre style="background:var(--md-sys-color-surface-container);padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;overflow-x:auto;font-size:0.85rem;margin:1rem 0"><code>{codeExample4}</code></pre>

      <h3 style="font-size:1.1rem;margin-top:1.5rem">5. Cloudflare R2 (Object Storage) ($0.15/GB, no egress)</h3>
      <p>S3 alternative with zero egress costs. Store user mission results, logs, generated artifacts.</p>
    </section>

    <section style="margin-bottom:2rem">
      <h2>The Real Economics</h2>
      <table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:1rem 0">
        <tr style="background:var(--md-sys-color-surface-container)">
          <th style="padding:0.75rem;text-align:left;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">Component</th>
          <th style="padding:0.75rem;text-align:left;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">Traditional</th>
          <th style="padding:0.75rem;text-align:left;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">Cloudflare</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">Compute (API)</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">$200/mo</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">$0 (under 100K/day)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">Database</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">$100/mo</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">$0 (D1 free tier)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">Cache/Sessions</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">$50/mo</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">$0 (KV free tier)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">Storage</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">$50/mo</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">$5 (R2 at scale)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">Monitoring</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">$100/mo</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">$0 (CF dashboard)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background:var(--md-sys-color-surface-container);font-weight:bold">
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">TOTAL (beta scale)</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">$500/mo</td>
          <td style="padding:0.75rem;border:1px solid var(--md-sys-color-outline)">$5/mo</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <p style="color:var(--md-sys-color-on-surface-variant)"><strong>Our actual spend (March 2026):</strong> $2.47/mo. We're on the free tier for everything except a tiny R2 bill.</p>
    </section>

    <section style="margin-bottom:2rem">
      <h2>What We Learned</h2>
      <ul style="color:var(--md-sys-color-on-surface-variant);line-height:1.8">
        <li><strong>Edge-first changes everything:</strong> No VPC, no connection pooling, no cold starts. Just instant global requests.</li>
        <li><strong>SQLite scales:</strong> D1 replicates your DB to every CF datacenter. Reads are local. Writes are replicated.</li>
        <li><strong>KV is your secret weapon:</strong> Rate limiting, sessions, temporary data—all at edge speed with no backend hits.</li>
        <li><strong>Monitoring is free:</strong> CF dashboard gives you metrics, errors, and analytics. You don't need expensive APM tools at this scale.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <div style="margin-top:3rem;padding:2rem;background:var(--md-sys-color-surface-container);border-radius:12px;text-align:center">
      <h3>Try Mekong RaaS Free</h3>
      <p style="color:var(--md-sys-color-on-surface-variant)">Deploy your own zero-cost SaaS. 10 free credits, no card required.</p>
      <md-elevated-button onclick="location.href='/'">Get Started</md-elevated-button>
    </div>
  </article>
</MainLayout>

<style>
